### ========================================
### VOYAGE — USER
### Execute os blocos de cima para baixo
### Os tokens são capturados automaticamente
### ========================================

@base = https://voyagegabi.onrender.com

@ownerToken  = {{loginOwner.response.body.token}}
@clientToken = {{loginClient.response.body.token}}
@adminToken  = {{loginAdmin.response.body.token}}

@ownerId  = {{createOwner.response.body.user.id}}
@clientId = {{createClient.response.body.user.id}}
@adminId  = {{createAdmin.response.body.user.id}}


### --- CRIAR USUÁRIOS ---

### 1. Criar owner
# @name createOwner
POST {{base}}/user HTTP/1.1
content-type: application/json

{
    "name":     "Maria Owner",
    "type":     "owner",
    "email":    "owner@voyage.com",
    "password": "B@tatinha123",
    "phone":    "19844450001",
    "cpf":      "275.484.389-23"
}

###

### 2. Criar client
# @name createClient
POST {{base}}/user HTTP/1.1
content-type: application/json

{
    "name":     "João Client",
    "type":     "client",
    "email":    "client@voyage.com",
    "password": "B@tatinha123",
    "phone":    "19844450002",
    "cpf":      "529.982.247-25"
}

###

### 3. Criar admin
# @name createAdmin
POST {{base}}/user HTTP/1.1
content-type: application/json

{
    "name":     "Ana Admin",
    "type":     "admin",
    "email":    "admin@voyage.com",
    "password": "B@tatinha123",
    "phone":    "19844450003",
    "cpf":      "403.609.150-60"
}

###


### --- LOGIN ---

### 4. Login owner
# @name loginOwner
POST {{base}}/user/login HTTP/1.1
content-type: application/json

{
    "email":    "owner@voyage.com",
    "password": "B@tatinha123"
}

###

### 5. Login client
# @name loginClient
POST {{base}}/user/login HTTP/1.1
content-type: application/json

{
    "email":    "client@voyage.com",
    "password": "B@tatinha123"
}

###

### 6. Login admin
# @name loginAdmin
POST {{base}}/user/login HTTP/1.1
content-type: application/json

{
    "email":    "admin@voyage.com",
    "password": "B@tatinha123"
}

###


### --- LEITURA ---

### 7. Listar todos os usuários (só admin pode)
GET {{base}}/user HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
content-type: application/json

###

### 8. Buscar por email
GET {{base}}/user?email=owner@voyage.com HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
content-type: application/json

###

### 9. Buscar por tipo
GET {{base}}/user?type=owner HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
content-type: application/json

###

### 10. Ver próprio perfil (owner)
GET {{base}}/user/{{ownerId}} HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{ownerToken}}
content-type: application/json

###

### 11. Ver próprio perfil (client)
GET {{base}}/user/{{clientId}} HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}
content-type: application/json

###

### 12. Admin vendo perfil de outro usuário
GET {{base}}/user/{{ownerId}} HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
content-type: application/json

###


### --- EDIÇÃO ---

### 13. Owner editando o próprio perfil
PUT {{base}}/user/{{ownerId}} HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{ownerToken}}
content-type: application/json

{
    "name":  "Maria Owner Editada",
    "phone": "19899990001"
}

###

### 14. Admin editando outro usuário
PUT {{base}}/user/{{clientId}} HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
content-type: application/json

{
    "name": "João Client Editado"
}

###


### --- DELEÇÃO ---

### 15. Deletar usuário (admin)
### ATENÇÃO: descomente só quando quiser apagar de verdade
# DELETE {{base}}/user/{{clientId}} HTTP/1.1
# Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
# content-type: application/json

###


### --- ERROS ESPERADOS ---

### 16. Login com senha errada (401)
POST {{base}}/user/login HTTP/1.1
content-type: application/json

{
    "email":    "owner@voyage.com",
    "password": "SenhaErrada@99"
}

###

### 17. Client tentando listar todos os usuários (403)
GET {{base}}/user HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}
content-type: application/json

###

### 18. Client tentando ver perfil de outro (403)
GET {{base}}/user/{{ownerId}} HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}
content-type: application/json

###

### 19. Requisição sem token (401)
GET {{base}}/user/{{ownerId}} HTTP/1.1
content-type: application/json

###
